2. (2) date, appointment, engagement -- (a meeting arranged in advance; "she asked how to avoid kissing at the end of a date")
3. (2) betrothal, troth, engagement -- (a mutual promise to marry)
4. (1) employment, engagement -- (the act of giving someone a job)
5. (1) engagement, booking -- (employment for performers or performing groups that lasts for a limited period of time; "the play had bookings throughout the summer")
